  <section class="bg-evium-dark py-28">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-12">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <div class="text-evium-green text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">Questions & Answers</div>
        <h2 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-black text-white leading-tight">
          Everything You Need to Know
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <details class="group bg-evium-dark-light rounded-2xl border border-white/8 overflow-hidden">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 p-7 cursor-pointer list-none select-none hover:bg-white/3 transition-colors duration-200">
            <span class="text-white font-semibold text-base">What exactly is the NEVI program?</span>
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full border border-white/20 flex items-center justify-center text-white/50 group-open:bg-evium-green group-open:border-evium-green group-open:text-evium-dark transition-all duration-200">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-3.5 h-3.5 group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform duration-200" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 4v16m8-8H4" />
              </svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-7 pb-7">
            <p class="text-white/55 text-sm leading-relaxed">NEVI — the National Electric Vehicle Infrastructure Formula Program — is a $7.5 billion federal initiative funded by the 2021 Infrastructure Investment and Jobs Act. It distributes grants to states to build a national network of EV charging stations along designated Alternative Fuel Corridors. States then contract with Charging Point Operators (CPOs) like Evium to deploy, operate, and maintain the hardware. The goal is a reliable, publicly accessible charging station at least every 50 miles along major U.S. highways.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-evium-dark-light rounded-2xl border border-white/8 overflow-hidden">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 p-7 cursor-pointer list-none select-none hover:bg-white/3 transition-colors duration-200">
            <span class="text-white font-semibold text-base">Does my site qualify for NEVI funding?</span>
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full border border-white/20 flex items-center justify-center text-white/50 group-open:bg-evium-green group-open:border-evium-green group-open:text-evium-dark transition-all duration-200">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-3.5 h-3.5 group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform duration-200" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 4v16m8-8H4" />
              </svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-7 pb-7">
            <p class="text-white/55 text-sm leading-relaxed">Eligibility depends on your proximity to a federally designated Alternative Fuel Corridor, your state's NEVI program status, utility capacity at the site, and other technical criteria. Gas stations, travel plazas, rest areas, truck stops, and retail sites near highway exits are common candidates. The fastest way to find out is through Evium's free site assessment — we'll evaluate your location and tell you within days whether you qualify and which programs apply.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-evium-dark-light rounded-2xl border border-white/8 overflow-hidden">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 p-7 cursor-pointer list-none select-none hover:bg-white/3 transition-colors duration-200">
            <span class="text-white font-semibold text-base">What does this cost me as a site host?</span>
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full border border-white/20 flex items-center justify-center text-white/50 group-open:bg-evium-green group-open:border-evium-green group-open:text-evium-dark transition-all duration-200">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-3.5 h-3.5 group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform duration-200" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 4v16m8-8H4" />
              </svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-7 pb-7">
            <p class="text-white/55 text-sm leading-relaxed">Under the NEVI no-cost model, the answer is nothing. Federal and state grant funding covers 100% of hardware costs, installation, permitting, utility upgrades, and commissioning. Evium also covers ongoing software, maintenance, and compliance costs. You provide the site and the electrical access point — Evium and the grant program cover everything else. Some site owners choose to co-invest for larger deployments or premium placement; we offer multiple financial models depending on your goals.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-evium-dark-light rounded-2xl border border-white/8 overflow-hidden">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 p-7 cursor-pointer list-none select-none hover:bg-white/3 transition-colors duration-200">
            <span class="text-white font-semibold text-base">Who handles maintenance when something breaks?</span>
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full border border-white/20 flex items-center justify-center text-white/50 group-open:bg-evium-green group-open:border-evium-green group-open:text-evium-dark transition-all duration-200">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-3.5 h-3.5 group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform duration-200" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 4v16m8-8H4" />
              </svg>
            </span>
